{"title":"Combined feed","url":"https://leoshcn.github.io/feeds/all.xml","elements":[{"title":"Archibald John Davies (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that stained glass artist <b><a href=\"/wiki/Archibald_John_Davies\" title=\"Archibald John Davies\">Archibald John Davies</a></b> ran a studio for 47 years at <a href=\"/wiki/Bromsgrove_Guild_of_Applied_Arts\" title=\"Bromsgrove Guild of Applied Arts\">Bromsgrove Guild of Applied Arts</a>, producing hundreds of works <i>(example pictured)</i><span style=\"padding-left:0.15em;\">?</span>","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Archibald_John_Davies","retrieved":1775239111072},{"title":"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the author of <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Unexpectedly_Naughty_Fukami\" title=\"Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami\">Unexpectedly Naughty Fukami</a></b></i> felt that the idea for the story was cliché when it was first suggested by her editors?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unexpectedly_Naughty_Fukami","retrieved":1775239111073},{"title":"a busy hospital in the capital of Malawi (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Bwaila_Hospital\" title=\"Bwaila Hospital\">a busy hospital in the capital of Malawi</a></b> handles 24,000 births per year by having ten babies in a bed and up to four in an incubator?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bwaila_Hospital","retrieved":1775239111075},{"title":"Kathryn Johnson (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that as the only woman reporter in her bureau, <b><a href=\"/wiki/Kathryn_Johnson_(journalist)\" title=\"Kathryn Johnson (journalist)\">Kathryn Johnson</a></b> was assigned to cover stories her male colleagues refused, such as the activities of Martin Luther King Jr.?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Kathryn_Johnson_(journalist)","retrieved":1775239111077},{"title":"Serious Sam II (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that the publisher of <i><b><a href=\"/wiki/Serious_Sam_II\" title=\"Serious Sam II\">Serious Sam&nbsp;II</a></b></i> petitioned <i><a href=\"/wiki/Guinness_World_Records\" title=\"Guinness World Records\">Guinness World Records</a></i> to recognise it for the most enemies simultaneously displayed in a video game?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Serious_Sam_II","retrieved":1775239111090},{"title":"Clara E. Thoms (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/Clara_E._Thoms\" title=\"Clara E. Thoms\">Clara E. Thoms</a></b> toured the United States as a concert pianist at the age of eight?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Clara_E._Thoms","retrieved":1775239111094},{"title":"a solar eclipse (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that two ancient Chinese astronomers are said to have been executed for failing to predict <b><a href=\"/wiki/Solar_eclipse_of_October_22,_2137_BC\" title=\"Solar eclipse of October 22, 2137 BC\">a solar eclipse</a></b> because they were drinking?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Solar_eclipse_of_October_22,_2137_BC","retrieved":1775239111097},{"title":"Vojin Đuričić (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that Yugoslav finance minister <b><a href=\"/wiki/Vojin_%C4%90uri%C4%8Di%C4%87\" title=\"Vojin Đuričić\">Vojin Đuričić</a></b> also headed an astronomical society and an aero club?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vojin_%C4%90uri%C4%8Di%C4%87","retrieved":1775239111097},{"title":"SHeDAISY (Wikipedia — did you know?)","contents":"... that <b><a href=\"/wiki/SHeDAISY\" title=\"SHeDAISY\">SHeDAISY</a></b><span class=\"nowrap\">'s</span> record label sent <a href=\"/wiki/Spatula\" title=\"Spatula\">spatulas</a> to radio programmers to encourage them to \"flip\" a poorly-received single?","link":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/SHeDAISY","retrieved":1775239111100},{"title":"Destination of the Month (Wikivoyage recommendations)","contents":"<style data-mw-deduplicate=\"TemplateStyles:r4523569\" typeof=\"mw:Extension/templatestyles mw:Transc